{"id":38,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":38,"title":"Chapter 35: Captain Moroni and Pahoran","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 35"],["h1","Captain Moroni and Pahoran"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p3"},"Captain Moroni was happy to hear that Helaman and his army had taken back much of the Nephite land from the Lamanites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/59.1"},"Alma 59:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p5"},"But Helaman and his army needed help. They did not have enough soldiers to defend so many cities."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/58.32"},"Alma 58:32"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p7"},"Captain Moroni wrote a letter to Pahoran, the chief judge and governor. He asked Pahoran to send more soldiers to help Helaman’s army."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/59.3"},"Alma 59:3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p9"},"The Lamanites attacked a Nephite city that Helaman had taken back. They killed many Nephites and chased the rest from the city."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/59.5-8"},"Alma 59:5–8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p11"},"Angry with the government leaders because they had not sent help, Moroni wrote another letter to Pahoran."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/59.13"},"Alma 59:13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/60.1"},"Alma 60:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p13"},"Captain Moroni wrote that many people had been killed because Pahoran had not sent more soldiers."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/60.5"},"Alma 60:5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p15"},"If Pahoran did not quickly send men and food, Moroni would take his army to Zarahemla and take what his army needed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/60.34-35"},"Alma 60:34–35"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p17"},"Soon Moroni received a letter from Pahoran. He was very sad that Moroni and his armies were suffering."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/61.1-2"},"Alma 61:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p19"},"Pahoran told Moroni that a group of wicked Nephites called king-men did not want him to be chief judge. They had forced him and his supporters out of Zarahemla."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/61.3-5"},"Alma 61:3–5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p21"},"Pahoran added that he was gathering an army to try to take back Zarahemla."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/61.6-7"},"Alma 61:6–7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p23"},"The king-men had chosen a king to be their leader and had joined the Lamanites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/61.8"},"Alma 61:8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p25"},"Pahoran was not angry at what Moroni had written. He wanted the Nephites to be free too."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/61.9"},"Alma 61:9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p27"},"He asked Moroni to bring a few men to help him and said that if Moroni gathered more men along the way, the combined army could take back Zarahemla."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/61.15-18"},"Alma 61:15–18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p29"},"Captain Moroni was happy that Pahoran was still loyal to his country and still wanted freedom for his people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/62.1"},"Alma 62:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p31"},"With a few of his men, Moroni went to meet Pahoran. He carried the title of liberty, and thousands of men joined them along the way."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/62.3-5"},"Alma 62:3–5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p33"},"The combined armies of Moroni and Pahoran marched against Zarahemla. They killed the king of the wicked Nephites and captured his men."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/62.7-8"},"Alma 62:7–8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_038_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p35"},"Moroni then sent food and 12,000 soldiers to help the Nephite armies. These armies drove the Lamanites out, and there was peace again in the land."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-35-captain-moroni-and-pahoran.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/62.12-13,38-42"},"Alma 62:12–13, 38–42"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
